<br>
I had one fuel pump fail at 30,000, but this was due to the gas here being horrid and dirty. I've heard this from a lot of sources so I tend to trust shitty gas and not a car problem.<br>
<br>
At about 20,000 I had a wheel bearing start to go in the right front. It would make an odd noise during turns. Fixed under warranty in about 4 hours. These are the only 2 problems I've had.<br>
<br>
I have the 2000SE, 140hp 2 litre 4 cylinder. Its peppy and economic at the same time. If I keep my driving conservative I get about 500-550km out of a 45l fill with nothing but in city driving.<br>
<br>
If I drive like I'm playing need for speed then I get the blast of a light car with lots of oomph but I suck gas like neesha sucks back free bud lites. I've had it up to 200kph once (passing a long line of rv's on the way back from Calgary, between banff and lake louise). Had it up to 170ish quite a few times.<br>
<br>
At speed is a very quiet car. Stock stereo kicks much ass (no mp3 though). Lots of room when you put the rear &quot;seats&quot; down. Can fit two mountain bikes if you take the wheels off em first. The rear &quot;seats&quot; are great if you have really short friends. I mean midget short.<br>
<br>
About me and cars though, I've never owned a domestic vehicle and I prolly never will. Euro or asian for me. So take my opinions with that in mind.<br>
<br>
Edit: Oh yeah, if I were to buy a car right now it would be a hybrid. Or a bike. Or a bus pass. Gas is getting stupid. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www2.junction.net/~matchett/mullwell.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
